headline: Hasbro Q2 beat, MARA to raise $850M, Otis issues weak guidance
summary: Hasbro (HAS) beat expectations in its second quarter thanks to record sales of Magic: The Gathering. The company also raised its guidance. MARA Holdings (MARA) stock is plunging after the company announced plans to raise $850 million through interest-free convertible notes to pay down debt and buy more bitcoin. Otis Worldwide (OTIS) stock is falling after the company issued soft guidance due to weak demand for new equipment in China and the Americas. headline: Hasbro Lifts Outlook as Tariff Concerns Ease
summary: Hasbro raised its outlook for the year, in part citing an improved tariff backdrop.  The maker of Nerf blasters and Play-Doh said Wednesday that, while tariff rates remain fluid, they are more favorable than the steep levies first introduced earlier this year.  “We’ve incurred minimal tariff related expenses in our year-to-date results, as most of the impacted inventory is still sitting on the balance sheet and is yet to flow through the P&L,” Chief Financial Officer  Gina Goetter  said Wednesday on a call with analysts.
